I"á<p>I was looking for sets of data to play around with and I came across the <a href="http://www.wrps.on.ca/inside-wrps/corporate-planning-systems">Waterloo Regional Police Service</a> data that is available to the public. I created some graphs of the data for the reader to check out. The data was filtered for vehicle stops for the year 2015. Time and location data was plotted. If you are interested in the scripts used in generating the plots, then let me know.</p>

<p>The following image contains a sort of histogram that placed the stops in bins based on their time of day occurence in a 24 hour time span.</p>

<p><img src="https://szonov.com/assets/average_day_frequency.png" alt="image" /></p>

<p>The next image is similar to the previous one, except now it places the stops in bins based on the day of the year in a one year span.</p>

<p><img src="https://szonov.com/assets/year_frequency.png" alt="image" /></p>

<p>The next few images are of the location based frequency of vehicle stops based on an entire year.</p>

