<p>It can be hard to appreciate the number of stops done throughout the year by looking at the maps or previous histograms. The actual number of stops is over 40000. I will let the user make â€˜conclusionsâ€™ on their own. The purpose of the post was not for analysis but instead for a small example of visualization and turning a huge csv file into a some neat graphs and plots. I will also provide the disclaimer for the users to go to the <a href="http://www.wrps.on.ca/inside-wrps/corporate-planning-systems">Waterloo Regional Police Service</a> website if they want to learn more about the data and its limits.</p>

